<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1344" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[178,1086,1177,1434]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Length 
<quantity box="[499,567,1177,1199]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
. Body shiny and yellowish-red, head and free aabdominal tergites free three and four reddish, antennae yellowish-red with the two basal antennomeres yellow, yellowish-red legs. Reticulation of the fore-body strong, that of the three basal free tergitgites evident, on the remaining free tergites superficial. Puncturation of head and pronotum fine and evident, that of the elytra double, with sparse strong punctures on a densely and finely punctuate background. Pronotum with two strong discal punctures. Fourth free tergite of the male with a feeble median carina, fifth with four strong granules in a transverse row, 
<figureCitation box="[753,834,1382,1404]" captionStart="Figs 57-64" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1417,1437]" captionTargetBox="[184,1059,230,1406]" captionTargetId="figure-6@29.[178,1085,524,820]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 57-64: Habitus, aedeagus in lateral and ventral views, spermatheca. (57-60) Zyras (Camonia) pugnax nov.sp.; (61-64) Zyras (Camonia) civilis nov.sp. Habitus scale bar Fig. 57: 6 mm; Fig. 61: 5.5 mm, other scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5335323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5335323/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus 
<figureCitation box="[963,1081,1382,1404]" captionStart="Figs 57-64" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1417,1437]" captionTargetBox="[184,1059,230,1406]" captionTargetId="figure-6@29.[178,1085,524,820]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 57-64: Habitus, aedeagus in lateral and ventral views, spermatheca. (57-60) Zyras (Camonia) pugnax nov.sp.; (61-64) Zyras (Camonia) civilis nov.sp. Habitus scale bar Fig. 57: 6 mm; Fig. 61: 5.5 mm, other scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5335323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5335323/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Figs 58-59</figureCitation>
, spermatheca 
<figureCitation box="[310,389,1412,1434]" captionStart="Figs 57-64" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1417,1437]" captionTargetBox="[184,1059,230,1406]" captionTargetId="figure-6@29.[178,1085,524,820]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 57-64: Habitus, aedeagus in lateral and ventral views, spermatheca. (57-60) Zyras (Camonia) pugnax nov.sp.; (61-64) Zyras (Camonia) civilis nov.sp. Habitus scale bar Fig. 57: 6 mm; Fig. 61: 5.5 mm, other scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5335323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5335323/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Fig. 60.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[178,1085,1449,1588]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: In the secondary sexual characters of the first free abdominall tergite of the male, the new species is comparable to 
<emphasis box="[856,965,1479,1500]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="PACE R" box="[972,1085,1478,1500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref12388" refString="PACE R. (1988): Aleocharinae della Guinea-Bissau (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Boletim de la Sociedade portuguesa de Entomologia 99: 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1988">PACE 1988</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[243,395,1507,1529]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Guinea-Bissau</collectingCountry>
. The new species differs from 
<emphasis box="[765,883,1508,1529]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
in the transverse pronotum, while that of 
<emphasis box="[432,542,1538,1559]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
is as long as wide. In ventral view, the apex of the aedeagus of the new species is very narrow, that of 
<emphasis box="[700,808,1567,1588]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
very broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[178,1085,219,270]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1344">
E t y m o l o g y: The name of the new species derives from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[983,1057,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1344">pugnax</emphasis>
= warlike.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
